9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 711, L.D. 1089, “An Act to Permanently
10 Fund 55 Percent of the State's Share of Education by Establishing a Tax on Incomes of
11 More than $1,000,000”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Permanently Fund 55 Percent of the State's Share of Education by
14 Establishing a Tax on High-income Earners'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §15699 is enacted to read:
18 §15699. Fund for Public Prekindergarten to Grade 12 Education
19 1. Fund established. The Fund for Public Prekindergarten to Grade 12 Education,
20 referred to in this section as "the fund," is established as an interest-bearing account
21 administered by the department.
22 2. Revenue. The Treasurer of State shall deposit all revenue collected pursuant to Title
23 36, section 5111, subsection 7 from the income tax surcharge to fund education into the
24 fund according to the schedule in Title 36, section 5111, subsection 7. All interest earned
25 by the fund becomes part of the fund.
26 3. Use of fund. The commissioner shall use the fund to ensure the State meets or
27 exceeds the annual target established by section 15752, inclusive of prekindergarten
28 funding.
29 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §5681, sub-§5, as amended by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. XXX, §1
30 and affected by §15, is further amended to read:
31 5. Transfers to funds. Before January 1, 2025, no later than the 10th day of each
32 month, the State Controller shall transfer to the Local Government Fund 5% of the receipts
33 during the previous month from the taxes imposed under Title 36, Parts 3 and 8, and Title
34 36, section 2552, former subsection 1, paragraphs A to F and L, and credited to the General
