24 allocation program and programming costs of administering state-municipal revenue
25 sharing may be paid by the Local Government Fund. Twenty percent of the amounts
26 transferred to the Local Government Fund each month must be transferred to the
27 Disproportionate Tax Burden Fund and distributed pursuant to subsection 4‑B.
28 Sec. 3. 36 MRSA §5111, sub-§7 is enacted to read:
29 7. Income tax surcharge to fund education. An income tax surcharge is established
30 and administered as follows.
31 A. For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, in addition to any other tax
32 imposed by this chapter, a surcharge at the rate of 2% is imposed on that portion of the
33 taxpayer's Maine taxable income in excess of:
34 (1) For single individuals and married persons filing separate returns, $1,000,000;
35 (2) For heads of households, $1,500,000; and
36 (3) For individuals filing married joint returns or surviving spouses, $2,000,000.
37 B. All revenue collected under this subsection must be used to fund public
38 prekindergarten to grade 12 education and must be deposited each year into the Fund
39 for Public Prekindergarten to Grade 12 Education established in Title 20-A, section
40 15699 in accordance with this paragraph.
41 (1) Prior to January 1st of each year, the bureau shall estimate the annual revenue
42 to be collected from the surcharge for the immediately following calendar year.
Page 2 - 132LR1823(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 711, L.D. 1089
1 (2) On the first of each month, beginning on January 1, 2026, the Treasurer of State
2 shall deposit 8.333% of the estimated annual total revenue from the surcharge into
3 the Fund for Public Prekindergarten to Grade 12 Education.
4 (3) The bureau may adjust the monthly transfer amount once annually to account
5 for any difference between the estimated collection and actual collection of
6 revenue for the year in which the transfer is made and any tax years prior to that
7 year.
8 Sec. 4. 36 MRSA §5160, as amended by PL 2003, c. 390, §35, is further amended
9 to read:
10 §5160. Imposition of tax
11 The tax is imposed, at the rates provided by section 5111, including the surcharge
12 imposed pursuant to section 5111, subsection 7, for single individuals, upon the Maine
13 taxable income of estates and trusts. The tax must be paid by the fiduciary.
14 Sec. 5. 36 MRSA §5403, sub-§8, as amended by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. ZZZ, §9, is
15 further amended to read:
16 8. Personal exemption phase-out. Beginning in 2018 and each year thereafter, by
17 the dollar amount of the applicable amounts specified in section 5126‑A, subsection 2,
18 paragraphs A, B and C, except that for the purposes of this subsection, notwithstanding
19 section 5402, subsection 1‑B, the "cost-of-living adjustment" is the Chained Consumer
20 Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30th of the preceding calendar year
21 divided by the Chained Consumer Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30,
22 2017; and
23 Sec. 6. 36 MRSA §5403, sub-§9, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. ZZZ, §10, is
24 amended to read:
25 9. Dependent exemption tax credit amount. Beginning in 2024 and each year
26 thereafter, by the dollar amount of the dependent exemption tax credit under section
27 5219‑SS, except that for the purposes of this subsection, notwithstanding section 5402,
28 subsection 1‑B, the "cost-of-living adjustment" is the Chained Consumer Price Index for
29 the 12-month period ending June 30th of the preceding calendar year divided by the
30 Chained Consumer Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30, 2023. If the credit
31 amount, adjusted by application of the cost-of-living adjustment, is not a multiple of $5,
32 any increase must be rounded to the next lowest multiple of $5.; and
33 Sec. 7. 36 MRSA §5403, sub-§10 is enacted to read:
34 10. Income tax surcharge. Beginning in 2026 and each year thereafter, by the dollar
35 amounts specified in section 5111, subsection 7, paragraph A, subparagraphs (1), (2) and
36 (3), except that for the purposes of this subsection, notwithstanding section 5402,
37 subsection 1‑B, the "cost-of-living adjustment" is the Chained Consumer Price Index for
38 the 12-month period ending June 30th of the preceding calendar year divided by the
39 Chained Consumer Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30, 2025.
